<p>April 1917<br/>8th   The weather has been gloriously fine all day (<strike>Easter Sunday</strike>) &amp; about half a dozen of us went into Bap<strike>p</strike> aume to-night.<br/>There is a "picture show" there but to-day being Easter Sunday, it was closed.  We heard to-day that we have brought out a new aeroplane, much supperior to Fritz's, &amp; it is expected that he is in for a bad time.  A very heavy bombardment started this afternoon about 4 P.M. on our left, &amp; lasted through the night.<br/>9th   <strike>The offensive</strike> Bad weather again to-day, hail &amp; rain &amp; a bighting cold wind.<br/>The bombardment continued this morning until about dinner time.   I have been out salvaging timber</p>
